Born and raised in Rancho San Diego, I spent most of my childhood either playing some sort of video game or skateboarding with my friends. My first discovery of any type of wed developement was fixing up my Myspace. Although it's the most basic of CSS, I always loved doing it. I've been working in the Shipping/Receiving industry for nearly 14 years, but I decided mid 2020 that I needed a change. Insert the UCSD Bootcamp Program! My hobbies still include playing video games, but I've retired the skateboarding. When I'm not behind a computer, you can catch me at a local bar or restaurant, or camping with my buddies. Nothing beats sitting around a campfire, beer in hand, and stories to tell. I current reside in Hillcrest, along with my lovely girlfriend, and our menegerie of animals. We're the proud pet parents of three cats: Zero, Gambit, and Rogue, as well as a female two year old English Mastiff: Bear!
